ue recognition in accordance with applicable standards. Manage the quarterly and annual budgeting processes Help prepare financial presentation materials for Board of Directors\u2019 meetings Help create materials with financial highlights that executive leaders may present to investors on a quarterly basis Collaborate with senior leadership and other departments on accounting policies, compliance requirements, and business needs Manage outside bookkeeper and hire additional personnel, if necessary Lead and continue to build a team of accounting professionals focused on accuracy, efficiency, scale, and cross functional partnership Assist outside tax accountant with preparation of annual income tax and related returnsRequired Skills and Experience Minimum 7 years operating in a professional accounting or controller role in software/technology or financial services Experience in a growth-stage startup environment, big plus if prior experience with pre-IPO technology company; fintech preferred Experience in financial statement preparation & analysis Knowledge of accounting systems (i.e. QuickBooks and/or ERP solutions): familiarity with QuickBooks, or similar small accounting systems, plus for prior experience leading an ERP conversion Ability to learn and implement new systems for accounting for digital assets Strong accounting knowledge, particularly in the technology space (e.g., software revenue recognition, digital or other financial assets accounting) Expertise in Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP) Able to manage operational tasks as well as set up internal controls for the company Ability to navigate a cross-functional organization and create a culture of collaboration between accounting and the rest of the company Bachelor\u2019s degree in Accounting or FinanceDesired Skills and Knowledge CPA (active or inactive) Public accounting experience highly desired Experience in maintaining compliance requirements (FINRA, MTL, SEC, FDIC, etc. ) Interest in 